structure.data:
Holiday Library Hours ~ December 22, 1997 - January 4, 1998

On this page: Catalogues | Services | Web Research Resources | Directories & News | Other Libraries

UTLink Catalogues, Journal Indexes, and Other Databases

  • UTLink catalogues and databases on the web
    We're pleased to announce that, in addition to our catalogue and journal indexes, hundreds of full text journals are now available to the university community via the web. We welcome your comments about this new service. User restrictions apply to some databases.

  • UTLink catalogues by telnet
    Telnet to the UTLink databases. The same databases as above are available, but with somewhat different commands and options for conducting your search. Please note: at the Username: prompt type UTLINK.

    Windows Netscape users who have difficulty making a telnet connection should consult Using Telnet with Netscape for Windows.

  • Electronic Resources (CD-ROM and online databases) in the U of T Libraries
[ Top of page]

Library Services

For services not listed below, please contact the appropriate library. Telephone numbers, addresses, and hours are available in the Guide to University of Toronto and Local Libraries

  • New Photo ID Library Card

  • Borrower Information
    To see which items you currently have charged out, to renew books, to review your fines record, or to see the status of holds you have placed, please:
    1. Select UTCatalogues by Telnet, above
    2. From the main UTLink menu, select 1 for UTCat
    3. Select the UTLink Options menu

  • UTLink Online Reference Service
    Send us your reference questions online.

  • Course-Related Library Materials

  • Alumni Services

  • Connecting to the Internet at UofT: UTORdial and UTORmail
    University of Toronto Libraries and Information Commons.
    Create, modify, and review your UTORdial account (for dial-up Internet connections at the University) and UTORmail account (for sending and receiving email).

  • Robarts Library carrel and locker application
    Apply for your carrel online.

  • UTLearn: Library and Internet Instruction (including Library and Academic Know How)
    Instruction Schedules, Directory of Instructors, Library and Internet Guides, and Related Resources
    Tutorials for UTCat, Medline and other journal indexes, and internet searching tools.

  • Send us your comments and suggestions
[ Top of page]

Web Research Resources

  • Desktop References - dictionaries, handbooks, etc.

  • Resources by subject

  • Resources by type

  • University of Toronto resources

  • Internet Guides
[ Top of page]

Directories and News: University of Toronto Library

  • Guide to University of Toronto and Local Libraries
    Hours, locations, phone numbers, collections, and other information about University of Toronto and local libraries.

  • Location Code Abbreviations used in UTCat

  • Engineering Library New Books

  • University of Toronto Libraries Staff Email Directory

  • Canada 411 (Bell Canada): Canadian phone numbers and addresses.
  • Postal Code Lookup (Canada Post)

  • University of Toronto Libraries Frequently Asked Questions

  • ITS Happening
    News about innovations and advances in information technology at the University of Toronto Libraries. Published by Information Technology Services.

  • University of Toronto Library. Library Council
    Membership, terms of reference, goals, standing committees and memoranda.

  • Task Force On Collection Development In The Sciences

  • University of Toronto Library Working Group on Undergraduate Library Services. Report.

  • CAN-LINKED Initiative
    A proposal for the co-ordinated development of a distributed national digital library system in Canada, prepared by a group of academic and research libraries. Jointly authored by C. Moore, Chief Librarian, University of Toronto, and Graham Hill, Chief Librarian, McMaster University.
[ Top of page]

Other Libraries: Information and Connections

  • Ontario College and University Library Directory
    University of Waterloo.
    Locations, phone numbers, collections, and contacts.

  • Webcats: Library Catalogues on the World Wide Web
    University of Saskatchewan.
    Web connections to online catalogues for academic and other libraries worldwide.

  • Other library catalogues: Hytelnet
    University of Saskatchewan.
    Telnet connections to online catalogues for academic and other libraries worldwide.

    Windows Netscape users who have difficulty making a telnet connection should consult Using Telnet with Netscape for Windows.

[ Top of page]

accessibility.title: Accessibility
accessibility.description: These checks highlight opportunities to [improve the accessibility of your web app](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/accessibility). Only a subset of accessibility issues can be automatically detected so manual testing is also encouraged.
accessibility.manualDescription: These items address areas which an automated testing tool cannot cover. Learn more in our guide on [conducting an accessibility review](https://developers.google.com/web/fundamentals/accessibility/how-to-review).

Technologies.Name: UTF-8
Technologies.Description: UTF-8 (8-bit UCS/Unicode Transformation Format) is a variable-length character encoding for Unicode. It is the preferred encoding for web pages.

Technologies.Name: Cascading Style Sheets
Technologies.Description: Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) is a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in a markup language. Its most common application is to style web pages written in HTML
